  "text": "## SSO Settings API Control: End-to-End Implementation\n\nGrafana's SSO settings control (`ssoSettingsApi` feature flag) implements a comprehensive, multi-layered architecture that gates the entire Single Sign-On settings infrastructure. This control extends from feature flag definition through to API endpoints, OAuth connector wiring, and access control enforcement.\n\n### Layer 1: Feature Flag Definition\n\nThe `ssoSettingsApi` feature flag is centrally defined in **pkg/services/featuremgmt/registry.go** (lines 933-941) with metadata:\n- **Name**: \"ssoSettingsApi\"\n- **Description**: \"Enables the SSO settings API and the OAuth configuration UIs in Grafana\"\n- **Stage**: FeatureStageGeneralAvailability (GA)\n- **Expression**: \"true\" (enabled by default)\n- **AllowSelfServe**: true (users can enable/disable)\n- **FrontendOnly**: false (affects backend functionality)\n- **Owner**: identityAccessTeam\n\nThis registry entry is automatically processed by Grafana's feature management pipeline to generate:\n- **pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.go**: Go constant `FlagSsoSettingsApi = \"ssoSettingsApi\"`\n- **packages/grafana-data/src/types/featureToggles.gen.ts**: TypeScript interface property `ssoSettingsApi?: boolean`\n- **pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.csv**: CSV format for internationalization and documentation\n- **pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.json**: JSON representation for API exposure\n\n### Layer 2: SSO Settings Infrastructure\n\nThe SSO settings infrastructure establishes two core interfaces in **pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettings.go**:\n\n**Service Interface** (lines 15-37):\n- `List()`, `ListWithRedactedSecrets()`: Retrieve all SSO settings\n- `GetForProvider()`, `GetForProviderWithRedactedSecrets()`: Retrieve settings for specific provider\n- `Upsert()`: Create or update SSO settings with audit trail\n- `Delete()`: Soft-delete SSO settings\n- `Patch()`: Update key-value pairs in SSO settings\n- `RegisterReloadable(provider string, reloadable Reloadable)`: Register a provider for live configuration reloading\n- `Reload(ctx context.Context, provider string)`: Trigger configuration reload\n\n**Reloadable Interface** (lines 39-45):\n- `Reload(ctx context.Context, settings SSOSettings) error`: Validate and apply new settings to the provider\n- `Validate(ctx context.Context, settings, oldSettings SSOSettings, requester) error`: Validate configuration changes before persistence\n\nThe **SSOSettings data model** in **pkg/services/ssosettings/models/models.go** (lines 46-54) uses xorm ORM annotations:\n- `ID`: Primary key\n- `Provider`: OAuth provider identifier\n- `Settings`: Map[string]any for flexible configuration\n- `Created`, `Updated`: Timestamps\n- `IsDeleted`: Soft-delete flag\n- `Source`: Enum indicating DB or System source\n- **Table name**: \"sso_setting\" (line 57)\n\nJSON serialization automatically converts settings keys from snake_case to camelCase for API responses (lines 61-77), enabling safe handling of provider-specific configuration parameters.\n\nThe **SSOSettingsStore** in **pkg/services/ssosettings/database/database.go** (lines 20-30) provides database persistence:\n- `ProvideStore(sqlStore db.DB) *SSOSettingsStore`: Factory function creating the store\n- Implements `ssosettings.Store` interface with `Get()`, `List()`, `Upsert()`, `Delete()` methods\n- Uses xorm's `UseBool()` utility for safe boolean queries on the `is_deleted` column\n- Handles transactional queries via `sqlStore.WithDbSession()`\n\nDatabase schema is managed via **pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ssosettings/migrations.go**, ensuring schema compatibility across versions.\n\nKubernetes API types in **pkg/apis/iam/v0alpha1/types_sso.go** define `SSOSettingSpec` for native Grafana resource management and future declarative configuration.\n\n### Layer 3: API & Authentication Wiring\n\nThe REST API is defined in **pkg/services/ssosettings/api/api.go** and conditionally registered only when the flag is enabled:\n\n**API Structure** (lines 30-43):\n- `ProvideApi()`: Factory function creating the API handler\n- `RegisterAPIEndpoints()`: Routes registration at `/api/v1/sso-settings` (line 63)\n\n**Routes** (lines 62-76):\n- `GET /api/v1/sso-settings/`: List all SSO settings (requires `ActionSettingsRead`)\n- `GET /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Get settings for specific provider (requires `ActionSettingsRead` with scope)\n- `PUT /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Update provider settings (requires `ActionSettingsWrite` with scope)\n- `DELETE /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Remove provider settings (requires `ActionSettingsWrite` with scope)\n\nEach endpoint is protected by the access control middleware, enforcing OAuth provider-specific scopes (`ActionSettingsRead` / `ActionSettingsWrite` with `ScopeSettingsOAuth(provider)`).\n\nIn **pkg/api/api.go**, the main route handler conditionally registers the SSO settings authentication UI:\n- **Lines 231-237**: `adminAuthPageEvaluator` uses `EvalAuthenticationSettings()` for LDAP/SAML, and when `FlagSsoSettingsApi` is enabled, adds `OauthSettingsEvaluator()` for OAuth settings access\n- **Lines 241-244**: When the flag is enabled, registers the admin authentication provider page at `/admin/authentication/:provider` with provider-scoped access control\n\nThe **SocialService** in **pkg/login/social/socialimpl/service.go** (lines 56-58) loads OAuth connectors:\n```go\nif features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n    allSettings, err := ssoSettings.List(context.Background())\n    // OAuth connectors use these settings for dynamic configuration\n}\n```\n\nEach OAuth connector registers itself as a `Reloadable` when the flag is enabled:\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/google_oauth.go** (lines 61-62): `NewGoogleProvider()` calls `ssoSettings.RegisterReloadable(social.GoogleProviderName, provider)`\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/github_oauth.go** (lines 77-79)\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/okta_oauth.go** (lines 56-58)\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/gitlab_oauth.go** (lines 59-61)\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/generic_oauth.go** (lines 70-72)\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/azuread_oauth.go** (lines 91-93)\n- **pkg/login/social/connectors/grafana_com_oauth.go** (lines 49-51)\n\nEach connector implements the `Reloadable` interface:\n- `Validate()`: Validates OAuth configuration (e.g., required fields, URL formats)\n- `Reload()`: Applies new OAuth settings to the provider instance\n\nLDAP provider registration in **pkg/services/ldap/service/ldap.go** (lines 59-60):\n```go\nif s.features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) && s.features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsLDAP) {\n    s.ssoSettings.RegisterReloadable(social.LDAPProviderName, s)\n}\n```\n\nAuthentication client registration in **pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/registration.go** (lines 55-60):\n```go\nssoSettingsLDAP := features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) && features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsLDAP)\nif cfg.LDAPAuthEnabled || ssoSettingsLDAP {\n    ldap := clients.ProvideLDAP(cfg, ldapService, userService, authInfoService)\n    // LDAP authentication is registered conditionally\n}\n```\n\n### Layer 4: Access Control & Dependency Injection\n\nThe access control layer gates UI and API access through evaluators in **pkg/services/accesscontrol/ssoutils/utils.go**:\n\n**EvalAuthenticationSettings()** (lines 8-14):\nEvaluates permission for LDAP and SAML authentication configuration:\n```go\nreturn ac.EvalAny(\n    ac.EvalAll(\n        ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsWrite, ac.ScopeSettingsSAML),\n        ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead, ac.ScopeSettingsSAML),\n    ),\n    ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionLDAPStatusRead))\n```\n\n**OauthSettingsEvaluator()** (lines 17-24):\nDynamically evaluates OAuth-provider-specific permissions based on configured providers:\n```go\nfor provider := range cfg.SSOSettingsConfigurableProviders {\n    result = append(result, ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead, ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(provider)))\n    result = append(result, ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsWrite, ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(provider)))\n}\nreturn ac.EvalAny(result...)\n```\n\nThese evaluators are used in **pkg/services/navtree/navtreeimpl/admin.go** (lines 184-187) to gate the SSO settings admin UI:\n```go\nif authConfigUIAvailable && hasAccess(ssoutils.EvalAuthenticationSettings(s.cfg)) ||\n    (hasAccess(ssoutils.OauthSettingsEvaluator(s.cfg)) && s.features.IsEnabled(ctx, featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi)) {\n    // Add SSO settings nav link\n}\n```\n\nDependency injection is configured in **pkg/server/wire.go** (lines 381-382):\n```go\nssoSettingsImpl.ProvideService,\nwire.Bind(new(ssosettings.Service), new(*ssoSettingsImpl.Service)),\n```\n\nThe **ProvideService()** factory in **pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/service.go** (lines 47-100) orchestrates the complete SSO settings infrastructure:\n\n1. **Fallback Strategies** (lines 51-54): Loads configuration from:\n   - OAuth configuration via `NewOAuthStrategy(cfg)`\n   - LDAP configuration via `NewLDAPStrategy(cfg)`\n   - SAML configuration via `NewSAMLStrategy(settingsProvider)` (if licensed)\n\n2. **Provider Registry** (lines 61-75): Builds a list of available providers, conditionally adding:\n   - All OAuth providers: GitHub, GitLab, Google, Generic OAuth, Grafana Cloud, Azure AD, Okta\n   - LDAP (if `FlagSsoSettingsLDAP` is enabled)\n   - SAML (if licensed and `FlagSsoSettingsSAML` is enabled)\n\n3. **Store Creation** (line 77): `database.ProvideStore(sqlStore)` initializes the database layer\n\n4. **Service Initialization** (lines 79-90): Constructs the Service with:\n   - Configuration and database store\n   - Reloadable registry for dynamic provider configuration\n   - Configurable providers map from settings\n   - Secrets encryption service\n   - Prometheus metrics\n\n5. **Conditional API Registration** (lines 94-97):\n   ```go\n   if features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n       ssoSettingsApi := api.ProvideApi(svc, routeRegister, ac)\n       ssoSettingsApi.RegisterAPIEndpoints()\n   }\n   ```\n   Only registers REST API endpoints when the feature is enabled.\n\nSecrets handling in **pkg/services/secrets/migrator/migrator.go** ensures encrypted storage of sensitive OAuth credentials and LDAP passwords in the `sso_setting` table.\n\n### Control Flow Summary\n\nThe complete control flow demonstrates how `FlagSsoSettingsApi` gates all SSO settings functionality:\n\n1. **Feature Activation**: Flag set in registry\n2. **Infrastructure**: Service, Store, and Reloadable interfaces enable dynamic configuration\n3. **Provider Wiring**: Each OAuth/LDAP connector registers itself as reloadable when flag is enabled\n4. **API Exposure**: REST endpoints at `/api/v1/sso-settings` are only registered when flag is enabled\n5. **Access Control**: Feature flag + RBAC evaluators (`EvalAuthenticationSettings`, `OauthSettingsEvaluator`) control both API and UI access\n6. **DI Registration**: Wire dependency injection ensures all components are properly initialized\n\nThis multi-layered approach ensures that SSO settings management is fully gated at every level—configuration cannot leak into the system unless the flag is explicitly enabled and the user has appropriate role-based access control permissions."
